## TypeScript (Functions)

| File type | Target | Hard review threshold |
|-----------|--------|----------------------|
| Function handler | 150 lines | 250 lines |
| Service | 300 lines | 500 lines |
| Repository | 250 lines | 400 lines |
| Model/schema | 200 lines | 300 lines |
| Test file | 400 lines | 700 lines |

## Functions (methods)

- Target under 40 lines; mandatory review above ~60 lines
- Maximum nesting depth of three levels
- Prefer fewer than six parameters; use parameter objects for complex operations
- One responsibility per function

## Refactor when a file has

- Multiple unrelated classes or responsibilities
- Repeated conditional logic or deep nesting
- Excessive boolean flags or constructor dependencies
- UI, business logic and persistence together
- Protocol parsing mixed with game logic

## Prohibited artificial splitting

- One-line wrapper files
- Excessive micro-classes or meaningless abstractions
- Interfaces with one implementation and no architectural need
- Deep folder nesting without benefit

## Review checklist

- [ ] File size within thresholds or refactor justified
- [ ] Single clear responsibility per file
